{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"750331b7-dda5-457a-897d-8ed5b5d2a776","content":"`SafeAreaEdges` isn't a standard .NET MAUI `ContentPage` property. You likely need a combination of platform-specific settings:\n\n**1. iOS — disable safe area insets:**\n```xml\nxmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n\n<ContentPage ...\n    ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\">\n```\n\n**2. Android — opt into edge-to-edge rendering:**\nIn your `MainActivity.cs` (or via lifecycle events):\n```csharp\nusing AndroidX.Core.View;\n\n// In OnCreate, after base call:\nWindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window, false);\n```\n\n**3. Hide navigation chrome** (if using Shell or NavigationPage):\n```xml\nShell.NavBarIsVisible=\"False\"\n<!-- or -->\nNavigationPage.HasNavigationBar=\"False\"\n```\n\n**4. Make sure your Image fills the space:**\n```xml\n<Image Source=\"photo.jpg\"\n       Aspect=\"AspectFill\"\n       HorizontalOptions=\"Fill\"\n       VerticalOptions=\"Fill\" />\n```\n\nThe core issue is that each platform has its own opt-in mechanism for drawing behind system bars — there's no single cross-platform MAUI property that handles both today.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d48e5c39-64d0-494f-a420-25887ab59b4d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is working on a .NET MAUI app targeting .NET 10 and wants an image to go edge-to-edge (behind status bar and navigation bar). They've set `SafeAreaEdges=\"None\"` on the ContentPage but still see padding.\n\nThis is a common issue in .NET MAUI. Let me think about what they might be missing:\n\n1. In .NET MAUI, `IgnoreSafeArea` is the property that controls whether content extends behind system bars. But there's also the concept of safe area insets.\n\n2. Actually, in .NET MAUI for .NET 8+, there's `Page.IgnoreSafeArea` or similar properties. Let me think...\n   \nThe real issue is platform-specific: on iOS I need to disable safe area handling, while on Android the app needs to be configured to draw edge-to-edge with proper system window handling. The `SafeAreaEdges` property alone might not be sufficient—I should check if there's a platform-specific setting or if the page needs additional configuration to actually extend behind the system bars. I'm realizing that .NET MAUI's approach to edge-to-edge rendering varies by platform—iOS uses the `UseSafeArea` property set to false through platform-specific configuration, while Android requires lower-level window configuration like `SetDecorFitsSystemWindows` to disable system window insets, though the exact implementation depends on the .NET MAUI version being used. I'm wondering if .NET 9 or 10 introduced new APIs for edge-to-edge support that I should account for, though the user might also be referencing a community toolkit or misremembering the property name. The core issue is likely that they need platform-specific handling on iOS with `UseSafeArea=\"False\"` and explicit Android configuration, plus managing any navigation chrome from Shell or NavigationPage.\n\nFor the Image control, I should mention setting `Aspect` to `AspectFill` so it properly fills the edge-to-edge space.","outputTokens":1500,"requestId":"A859:1BCBFD:6F8691:80E4D6:69FBE54B"},"id":"85cedd6d-bf62-416f-a6ea-783699b521f8","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:05:46.696Z","parentId":"4414af8b-f2ba-4b3f-bbfc-f8538514426e"}
